news.title: Realty registrations dip in Kolkata in April as price hike makes buyers cautious
news.para: Real estate analysts said the slowdown in sales and registrations was a reflection of home buyers becoming cautious and postponing the purchase decision due to price hike.

news.title: Government to set up panel on RERA non-compliance
news.para: The government may also seek state governments to provide their inputs in this matter with an objective of making Rera more effective and offering an impactful recourse mechanism to homebuyers. The decision to this effect was taken in the recent meeting of the Central Advisory Council (CAC).

news.title: YEIDA orders forensic audit of Ajnara Panorama, to hire private firm
news.para: Through the audit, officials said, the Authority will get an assessment of the construction completed till now, apart from finding out the exact number of flats sold and possession given to buyers to date.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Shilp Group acquires 21,000 sq yard plot for Rs 200 crore in Gota
news.para: Market sources peg the deal size to be at Rs 200 crore. A luxury residential building is expected to come up on the plot bought by Shilp Group.

news.title: Gurugram: Soon, registry of floors on plots below 180 sq yd?
news.para: Due to restrictions by the state government on registering independent floors built on plots less than 180 sq yd in size in private developer areas, the owners can neither formally own them nor sell the property.

news.title: Noida: Not May, Supertech twin towers may be brought down only in August
news.para: While the Noida Authority has refused to extend the deadline, calling it a breach of the agreement, officials said Supertech, the developer, was planning to approach the Supreme Court with the private company’s request.

news.title: Holcim deal talks with Adani, JSW enter last leg
news.para: The third likely contender, Kumar Mangalam Birla's UltraTech, has not yet held any such deliberations, though it's pushing to join the fray despite anti-trust worries.

news.title: NCLAT allows ATS group firm to withdraw appeal after settlement with financial creditor
news.para: The NCLT had directed to initiate insolvency proceedings against the Noida-based ATS group firm over a plea filed by ICICI Prudential Venture, claiming a dues of Rs 25 crore. Ananda Divine Developers had challenged the order before the appellate tribunal.

news.title: Rajan Bharti Mittal sells south Delhi property for Rs 45 crore
news.para: Experts said the scarcity of such properties available for outright sale in prominent Delhi addresses will ensure that prices remain high despite market fluctuations in other parts of the city.

news.title: Canara Bank probes fraud in Can Fin Homes after whistleblower complaint: Source
news.para: "We decided to act on this complaint given the severity of the situation and found out that there were frauds in 37 accounts worth 39 million rupees ($504,149.54). We have made provisions of an equal amount," said the source, who declined to be named as the discussions were private.

news.title: Aadhar Housing Finance gets Sebi's nod to float IPO
news.para: Going by the draft papers, Blackstone-backed Aadhar Housing, which filed preliminary papers with Sebi in January last year, is looking to raise Rs 7,300 crore through its initial share sale.

news.title: Steel prices may fall to Rs 60,000 per tonne by March 2023: Crisil
news.para: In April, steel prices hit an all-time high of over ~Rs 76,000, which is ~95% over March 2020 levels, when Covid-19 was declared a pandemic.

news.title: Ind-Ra revises up commercial realty outlook for FY23
news.para: It said the impact of the third Covid wave has receded and the relaxation in COVID-19 restrictions has led to resumption of offices in the hybrid mode and retail spaces opening steadily, which will lead to a gradual recovery and growth of the sector.

news.title: After Nitin Gadkari's letter, NIT issued part OC to Glocal mall despite flaws
news.para: On April 8, 2022, NIT issued part OC to the mall even while pointing out that nine flaws were yet to be rectified by the builder. On April 29, NIT issued notice to 35 tenants, and within three days demolished their shops with infrastructure, electrical, electronic and other equipment, based on the part OC.

news.title: Ludhiana: Park sold off, probe begins after residents protest
news.para: Area councillor Pankaj Kaka said: “The fault lies with the developer who is accused of selling the park land to a private person. When S S Bindra was master town planner, he had reported it as ‘encroachment’ and recommended it to be removed.”
